              id: "eng-my-mother", unit: "Poetry Ch.1", title: "My Mother at Sixty-Six", marks: 3,
              hook: "In a car ride between Cochin and the airport, Kamala Das confronts the fear no child can name.",
              topics: ["Ageing and mortality", "Mother-daughter relationship", "Imagery: mother's pale face vs young trees/children", "Poet's fear and helplessness", "Bittersweet parting"],
